[assistant] Fixed the scripted SSH transport startup sequence.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - JSch `0.1.27` expects the server `SSH_MSG_KEXINIT` immediately after the version banner, before the client sends its own KEXINIT.
[assistant] - The previous scripted transport only queued the banner initially and waited for the client KEXINIT before queuing the server KEXINIT, causing JSch to read from an empty scripted stream and fail with `End of IO Stream Read`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made in `IdentityFileTest.java`:
[assistant] - The scripted transport now queues both:
[assistant]   - server version banner
[assistant]   - server KEXINIT packet
[assistant] - When the client KEXINIT later arrives, it records it for exchange-hash calculation but does not enqueue a duplicate server KEXINIT.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the tests.
[assistant-event] text_end
